pr_body:
Fixes #193 
Type: Enhancement

What's new?
Easy loading and sharing of palette as a ```.gpl``` extension file.
Press ```x``` to launch palette picker

![Screenshot from 2020-08-11 03-26-17](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/89835555-a04f3b80-db82-11ea-803a-91a3a4e2f3d6.png)

From #194 loading and saving of palette was introduced.

- Users can now open the palette config file ```.gpl``` with GIMP/ or can manually edit it.
- Options are now moved to Fractal -> Palette -> as ```Load Palette Config``` and ```Save Palette Config```

![Screenshot from 2020-08-12 00-08-49](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/89935696-35f4d480-dc30-11ea-9cd1-92c5f7a9b54f.png)

pr_title: Add current fractal information help menu
pr_body:
Fixes #164 

Added: ```Help -> Info on current fractal``` opens up the wiki for the current fractal at https://github.com/xaos-project/XaoS/wiki/Fractal-Types

Issue: #129 
Type: Enhancement

What's New?
Now users can render multiple files together using batch rendering option. The files names will be in format: (Base_Name)_(File_Number)_(XXXXX) - this means users can batch render animation files and xpf files together with no collisions.

Where to find the option?
Files -> Batch Render

UI: 
![Screenshot from 2020-07-09 12-59-58](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/87013780-c9c62180-c1e8-11ea-9d98-a03b7190f610.png)
![Screenshot from 2020-07-09 13-00-18](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/87013790-cdf23f00-c1e8-11ea-93fd-b49e1b5c669e.png)

Issue: Fixes #115 

Panning while rotation didn't used to work/ was erratic before XaoS 4.1. This fix solves it.
This fix first disables rotation only the first time panning starts, does panning, and continues rotation. On complex fractals with slower boundary trace users may face some loading time while starting panning.

pr_title: Unify open/ open image and save/ save image
pr_body:
Issue #190 

This PR unifies Open and Open Image menu options. Now ```Open``` is able to load png and xpf both.
Save Image has been shifted to ```Save as``` and  ```Save``` remains as it is.

![Screenshot from 2020-07-21 13-14-40](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/88027040-5e6b4080-cb54-11ea-8239-c556187cd3f8.png)
```Save as``` should get populated in future when xaos starts supporting more export formats.

Ps. Should we rename Save as to Export as ?

Type: Enhancement

Issues: Fixes #122 

What's New?
Cartesian Grid added.

How to use?
Go to View -> Cartesian grid -> Enable
Keyboard: Press 'g'

Sample:
![Screenshot from 2020-06-25 08-31-30](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/85668681-a4132580-b6dc-11ea-87ef-f2ccec229fd6.png)

Current Shortcomings:
Cartesian Grid is only available until 100000x zoom levels i.e. in coordinate axis terms not fractal zoom terms.

Ps. There is a small unrelated change to fix some bugs introduced by #169

Type: Enhancement
Part of #165 

What's new?
This PR will add feature for users to know beforehand the color palette going to be generated.

Where to see changes?
In GUI menu, Fractal->Palette->Custom Palette
 
![Screenshot from 2020-06-18 13-40-34](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5468342/84997026-abca4b80-b16b-11ea-8b26-caae4100a92c.png)

pr_title: Save xpf data in png chunk
pr_body:
Type : Enhancement
Fixes #128 

Changes:
Added option to 'Open Image' under File menu.T
This option allows to save & open PNG without XPF data.

pr_title: Do not use temporarily an XPF file when saving/loading from a PNG
pr_body:
Fixes #179 
Potential Fix for #174 (to be checked)

This removes dependency over temporary file used in ver 4.1 for saving images with xaos and reading them back.

Fixes #152 

This PR changes the size of buffer for filenames, this fixes the persisting issue.

pr_title: Fix Seg fault while rendering from cli
pr_body:
Rendering through command line produced seg fault errors due to assigning font to uih_context - gc1
 (NULL) when called from command line.
Fixed in this.

pr_title: Invalid Commands only produce error message
pr_body:
The last implementation shown help message along with error message on every unavailable commands.

Now the errors message is produced as:
```
> xaos -unavailable function
> unavailable function:unknown function
Please enter `xaos -help` to learn more on command line options
```

PS: This is part 1 of #155
